In contrast to the natural reservoir, the innate immune response in human infection is distinctly different. It has been shown that human infection with the viruses associated with HCPS, HPAI or SARS results in upregulation of the pro-inflammatory cytokines, a major contributing factor to increased disease severity (He et al., 2006; Szretter et al., 2007; Frieman et al., 2008; Peiris et al., 2009; Safronetz et al., 2011). In HPAI H5N1 virus infection of human alveolar epithelial cells, IL-6, IL-8 and IFN-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
